<HEADLINE>
<P>
J.F.K. PAPERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I am not a fan of conspiracy theories. Nevertheless, I was amazed that in your 
Associated Press article ("Graphic J.F.K. Assassination Car Photos, Records 
Released," May 4) the definite statement is made that the released documents 
"shed little additional light on the assassination." 
</P>
<P>
 This conclusion was reached one day after 50,000 documents in 224 boxes were 
released to the public.  
</P>
<P>
 JACK McNALLY 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale 
</P>
