<HEADLINE>
<P>
RUNWAY TO REALITY: BY DESIGN; NOT A MURPHY BROWN EXCLUSIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOANNA DENDEL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Look: The most elegant pantsuit has to be the one TV's Murphy Brown is so 
fond of -- double-breasted, with a plunging shawl collar. The most daring 
working girls wear nothing but an amazing necklace underneath. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Do It Big: Giorgio Armani does a rich lightweight wool crepe pantsuit in 
taupe, white, creme, navy and, of course, black. It costs $1,975. The glass 
bead lariat necklace is $350. At $16.50, the macrame shoulder bag is a bargain. 
The whole ensemble is available at the Giorgio Armani boutique on Rodeo Drive 
and at I. Magnin, both in Beverly Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Total price: $2,341.50. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Do It Budget: It's rare to find an inexpensive pantsuit that looks as if it's 
been made by expert Italian tailors. This jacket in a blend of 50% wool and 50% 
polyester is only $39.95 at the Hit or Miss store in Century City's ABC 
Entertainment Center. (A matching short skirt is $14.99.) The pleated pants in 
100% taupe wool gabardine are by San Francisco designer Ceceilia Hsu for CEZU. 
They're cut beautifully for $118, and can be special ordered through B. Magness 
in Newport Beach. The glass beaded necklace is a handmade concoction fashioned, 
for a total of $50, from a necklace, two bracelets and a pair of earrings from 
Pier 1 Imports, citywide. This $10 macrame bag is from Bun-Ka Do, a little shop 
in Little Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Total amount: $217.95. JOANNA DENDEL 
</P>
</TEXT>
