<HEADLINE>
<P>
EX-GOVERNOR'S WIDOW REJECTS RUN FOR SEAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The widow of former Gov. Richard Snelling ended speculation about her own 
gubernatorial bid, saying that she will seek reelection as lieutenant governor. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think this is the way I can serve Vermont best," Barbara Snelling said 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 As lieutenant governor in 1991, Dean became governor upon Snelling's death. 
There was speculation that Barbara Snelling would challenge Dean in 1992, but 
she ran instead for the No. 2 post, winning with 53% of the vote. 
</P>
