<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; POLICE SEEK MAN IN FATAL SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police are looking for a 46-year-old Ventura man in connection with a fatal 
shooting at a Ventura mobile home park. 
</P>
<P>
 Raul Cervantes Viveros, who witnesses said shot and killed his neighbor Juan 
Vargas on Sunday, has fled the area, Sgt. Bob Anderson said. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's still at large, and we're doing our best to locate him," Anderson said. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses at the Vargas home in the Victorian Park mobile home park said 
Viveros was drunk and began a fistfight with Vargas after the victim refused to 
turn down music at his house. 
</P>
<P>
 Vargas' wife, Racil, said that 10 minutes after the fight, the fieldworker 
left and returned with a shotgun, killing her husband. 
</P>
<P>
 Viveros' car was abandoned in the Wagon Wheel Road area of Oxnard, police 
said. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
