<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; WOMAN CHARGED WITH MOLESTING BOY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 35-year-old Thousand Oaks woman has been charged with 31 counts of child 
molestation for having sex almost once a month with a teen-age boy for 2 1/2 
years, prosecutors said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 With tears in her eyes, Gloria G. Goldman appeared for arraignment Wednesday 
in Ventura County Municipal Court.However, the arraignment was put off until 
May 20 and Goldman remains free in lieu of $10,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
 Goldman is charged with molesting the Thousand Oaks boy at least once a month 
from August, 1991, to February, 1993, with the exception of one month in 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 The alleged incidents began when the boy, now 17, was 15, the complaint says. 
</P>
<P>
 Goldman, a former teacher, faces 11 counts of a lewd act upon a child, 18 
counts of oral copulation and two counts of unlawful sexual intercourse. Deputy 
Dist. Atty. Bob Calvert declined to discuss the facts in the case, or whether 
authorities suspect any other boys are involved. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura County Sheriff's Deputy Bob LeMay said the victim revealed the alleged 
affair after recently converting to Christianity. 
</P>
<P>
 The boy initially told a church peer counselor, who reported it to 
investigators. The boy talked with authorities about three weeks ago, LeMay 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's emotionally troubled by the whole incident," LeMay said. The teen-ager 
has temporarily moved from the area, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The public defender's office was appointed to represent the woman. She left 
the courthouse without talking to reporters. DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</TEXT>
