<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: LAWNDALE; NEPOTISM LAW GETS PRELIMINARY CITY OK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT SANDELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has given preliminary approval to an ordinance designed to 
prevent nepotism at City Hall. 
</P>
<P>
 Council members voted 5 to 0 last week to prohibit the city from hiring 
relatives of the city manager, department heads and elected or appointed 
officials. 
</P>
<P>
 The ordinance also would bar relatives from working in the same department 
under certain circumstances. Current employees would not be affected as long as 
they remain in their present positions. 
</P>
<P>
 Unlike a previous draft, the proposed law would not prevent the appointment of 
relatives to committees. 
</P>
<P>
 A final vote is scheduled May 19. SCOTT SANDELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
