COMMUNITY NEWS: INGLEWOOD; MAN CONVICTED IN RAPE, MURDER CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES BENNING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 21-year-old Los Angeles man was convicted of murdering an Inglewood woman 
and molesting her preteen daughter in 1992, just two weeks after he had raped 
another woman. 
</P>
<P>
 Jurors on Tuesday found Deshawn Malone guilty of raping and murdering Davette 
Beatley, 36, in her Inglewood apartment in the November, 1992, attack. Malone 
also was convicted of raping another woman two weeks before he shot Beatley. 
</P>
<P>
 The trial's penalty phase, which began Wednesday in Los Angeles Superior 
Court, will determine whether Malone is sentenced to death or to life in prison 
without possibility of parole. JAMES BENNING 
