<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: TORRANCE; BEST BUY CO. TO OPEN STORE AT OLD GEMCO SITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY GUTHRIE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Best Buy Co. Inc. will make its Southern California debut this fall when the 
consumer electronics chain opens a store in the former Gemco building at 
Hawthorne Boulevard and Pacific Coast Highway. 
</P>
<P>
 The building has been vacant since Gemco went out of business more than five 
years ago. 
</P>
<P>
 The Torrance store will be the first of six to eight stores that the retailer 
says it will open in California by the end of the year. Best Buy currently has 
152 stores in 18 states. 
</P>
<P>
 Last week, the Torrance Planning Commission unanimously approved plans to 
renovate the 10 1/2-acre site. Merchandising Development USA Inc. owns the 
property, which it will lease to Best Buy. Another retail store would sublet 
part of the site, but Best Buy executives said they have not yet signed a 
subleasing agreement. 
</P>
<P>
 Best Buy sells electronics, computers and home appliances. Store employees are 
not paid on commission, and shoppers can help themselves to the merchandise 
stacked on the sales floor. 
</P>
<P>
 Best Buy will begin hiring 100 to 250 full- and part-time workers in 
September, company officials said. MARY GUTHRIE 
</P>
</TEXT>
