<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: RANCHO PALOS VERDES; CITY OPPOSES PROPOSED MTA BUS SERVICE CUTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rancho Palos Verdes officials oppose a proposal by the Los Angeles 
Metropolitan Transportation Authority to cut bus services on the Palos Verdes 
Peninsula. 
</P>
<P>
 The authority is considering service reductions on Routes 225, 226, and 444 to 
cut expenses.City administrative analyst Veronica Dolleschel said 11 of the 
authority's proposed 22 cutbacks in the 1994-95 budget could affect bus users 
on the peninsula. 
</P>
<P>
 Options include canceling operation of all three lines on Saturdays, canceling 
all Sunday and holiday service on the 444, and reducing the 225 and 226 service 
to one bus every two hours. 
</P>
<P>
 In a letter to the authority, Mayor Steven Kuykendall says the city has 
serious concerns about the proposed cuts. He suggests raising fares to maintain 
service. 
</P>
