<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXCEPT FOR EMPIRE LEAGUE, BASEBALL PLAYOFF RACES UNSETTLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS FOSTER, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Only in the Empire League is there certainty about the high school baseball 
playoffs heading into the final regular-season games today and Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 With one game left, nine Orange County leagues have races for postseason play. 
The Empire League is set: El Dorado, Katella and Esperanza have locked up the 
three spots. 
</P>
<P>
 Here is the somewhat muddled picture: 
</P>
<P>
 DIVISION I 
</P>
<P>
 EMPIRE -- Clinched: El Dorado (19-6, 11-3), Katella (16-8-1, 10-4), Esperanza 
(8-6, 13-11). 
</P>
<P>
 SOUTH COAST LEAGUE -- Clinched: (Mater Dei (16-7-1, 11-3). Undecided: 
Capistrano Valley (16-8, 8-6), El Toro (16-9, 8-6), Dana Hills (13-11-1, 8-6) 
and San Clemente (14-10, 7-7) are in the running for two playoff spots, and 
numerous tiebreakers could be involved. 
</P>
<P>
 SUNSET LEAGUE -- Clinched: Fountain Valley (22-2-1, 10-2-1). Undecided: 
Servite (14-9, 8-5), Huntington Beach (17-9, 7-6), Marina (17-9, 7-6), Edison 
(15-7-1, 6-6-1), Ocean View (13-11, 6-7) and Westminster (13-12, 6-7) are 
competing for two playoff spots, which could be determined by several 
tiebreaker rules. 
</P>
<P>
 DIVISION II 
</P>
<P>
 CENTURY -- Clinched: Canyon (19-5, 12-2), Villa Park (15-9, 9-5). Undecided: 
Foothill (11-13, 7-7) qualifies if it beats El Modena. Orange (14-10, 7-7) 
qualifies if it beats Santa Ana Valley and Foothill loses. 
</P>
<P>
 FREEWAY -- Clinched: Fullerton (19-5, 11-3), Sunny Hills (12-12-1, 8-6). 
Undecided: Troy (14-9, 7-7) qualifies if it beats Sunny Hills. Buena Park 
(11-11, 7-7) qualifies if it wins and Troy loses. 
</P>
<P>
 ORANGE -- Clinched: Brea-Olinda (20-3, 10-3), Valencia (11-11, 10-3). 
Undecided: If Savanna (9-14, 6-7) and Magnolia (9-11, 6-7) finish tied, Savanna 
qualifies. 
</P>
<P>
 DIVISION III 
</P>
<P>
 GARDEN GROVE -- Clinched: La Quinta (22-3, 13-0), Kennedy (17-8, 9-3). 
Undecided: The winner of Friday's game between Garden Grove (13-9, 7-5) and 
Bolsa Grande (11-11, 7-6) qualifies. 
</P>
<P>
 PACIFIC COAST -- Clinched: Trabuco Hills (18-6, 13-1), Century (16-7, 9-5). 
Undecided: If Estancia (12-12, 8-6) and Laguna Hills (12-12, 7-7) finish tied, 
Laguna Hills qualifies. 
</P>
<P>
 SEA VIEW LEAGUE -- Clinched: Tustin (20-5, 12-1). Undecided: Corona del Mar 
(17-7, 8-5), Woodbridge (11-14, 8-5), Santa Margarita (12-11, 8-5), Saddleback 
(13-11, 7-6) and Irvine (14-12, 7-6) are competing for two playoff spots with 
multiple scenarios possible. 
</P>
<P>
 DIVISION V 
</P>
<P>
 OLYMPIC -- Clinched: Whittier Christian (15-8, 11-1), Cerritos Valley 
Christian (12-5, 8-3). Undecided: If Calvary Chapel (15-8, 7-4) and Orange 
Lutheran (10-13, 6-5) finish tied, they will have a playoff game Saturday. 
</P>
