FOUR MORE WORLD CUP GAMES SELL OUT, BUT NONE IN DALLAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four more World Cup games have sold out on individual game tickets, raising 
the total to 34 in the 52-game tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 The latest individual ticket sellouts, announced Wednesday by the organizers, 
are Switzerland-Colombia at Stanford on June 26, Morocco-Netherlands at 
Orlando, Fla., on June 29; Belgium-Saudi Arabia at Washington on June 29 and 
the second-round game at the Rose Bowl on July 3. 
</P>
<P>
 No games have sold out in any price category in Dallas, where tickets went on 
sale Monday at TicketMaster outlets in addition to the telephone sale. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets for all games still are available under premium plans ranging from 
$425 to $4,750 per strip, depending on the site and the number of games. 
