<P>
ARKANSAS PUTS TWO MURDERERS TO DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A drifter convicted of killing a woman who fed him milk and cookies was 
executed Wednesday, as was a man who ignored a plea for mercy during an armed 
robbery. 
</P>
<P>
 Jonas Whitmore was pronounced dead at 8:08 p.m., a prison spokesman said. 
Edward Charles Pickens died from a lethal injection exactly an hour later. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the first time a state executed two people on the same day since the 
U.S. Supreme Court allowed states to restore the death penalty in 1976. 
</P>
