<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: INSURANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Allstate, Nationwide Mutual Accused of Discrimination: A fair housing group 
alleged that the companies discriminated against minorities in the sale of 
homeowners insurance.The National Fair Housing Alliance, which represents 
housing agencies in 35 states, said it filed complaints with the Department of 
Housing and Urban Development alleging that Allstate Corp. and Nationwide 
Mutual Insurance Co. violated the federal Fair Housing Act. The complaints were 
the result of an investigation in Chicago, Atlanta, Milwaukee and Louisville, 
Ky., that showed widespread discrimination, the group said. The companies said 
they have corporate policies that forbid discrimination. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA051294-0273 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 040971 </DOCID>
