 Because one of the goals of the Wellness Community is to improve quality of 
life by developing a positive attitude, a few guests focused on the lighter 
side of fashion. Shira Levy, the development director and outreach coordinator 
for the group, wore a denim jacket hand-painted with pinballs, flappers and 
even a "Tilt" warning. 
</P>
<P>
 Adel V. Rakhshani looked more like a house painter than a fine artist in his 
white cap, white shirt and white pants. His work was on display at a private 
reception for the underwriters of the event. 
