DOWNEY TO SANTA ANA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Greg Johnson, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Domino's Pizza has moved its western regional office to Santa Ana from Downey. 
</P>
<P>
 "A centralized location in Orange County and favorable leasing arrangements 
were strong factors in our decision to relocate," said John Howard, vice 
president of franchise operations for Domino's. 
</P>
<P>
 About 30 employees at the Downey office moved to Santa Ana earlier this month. 
The Domino's western region stretches from San Diego to Seattle and encompasses 
more than 800 outlets. 
</P>
