<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Greg Johnson, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Computer City Move: The Computer City store that opened in Garden Grove nearly 
five years ago has been "relocated to an existing, two-story location in Santa 
Ana" near South Coast Plaza, Computer City President Alan Bush said. 
</P>
<P>
 Customers who need technical service for products purchased at the Garden 
Grove store are being directed to the chain's Brea store.Bush tied the 
relocation to the fact that "there was tremendous customer overlap between the 
two stores." 
</P>
<P>
 All but two of Computer City's Garden Grove employees have taken jobs at other 
company locations, Bush said, and the chain mailed out 85,000 notices to alert 
customers to the change.  
</P>
<P>
 "It's not like we're moving out of town," Bush said. "To the contrary, we're 
planning to open our sixth and seventh stores (in Southern California) very 
soon." 
</P>
