<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOPICS / BRIEFLY; RELIGION: WOMAN NAMED SENIOR RABBI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The leadership of Temple Emanuel, whose membership voted down a proposed 
merger with Wilshire Boulevard Temple last year, has named Laura Geller to be 
senior rabbi of the Beverly Hills temple. 
</P>
<P>
 The appointment was said to mark the first time a woman has become head of a 
major urban Jewish congregation. 
</P>
<P>
 Geller, currently executive director of the American Jewish Congress, is the 
third woman ever ordained as a rabbi by the Reform movement, one of three major 
branches of Judaism. 
</P>
