<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: VENICE; HOUSING AGENCY WORKER GIVES OF HERSELF: $50,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEN ELLINGWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Heidi Frey normally hunts for big donations to help the Venice Community 
Housing Corp. buy property for affordable housing. 
</P>
<P>
 Now, she and her husband, Robert Greenwald, have made one. 
</P>
<P>
 The couple's $50,000 contribution last Friday is about half of the cash the 
nonprofit corporation will need to buy and renovate a four-unit Oakwood 
building for low-income renters. The total cost of the project is estimated at 
$290,000, most of which will come from loans, said Steve Clare, the 
corporation's executive director. 
</P>
<P>
 Frey, a screenwriter, is a member of the corporation's fund-raising committee. 
She and her husband, a director and producer, live in Venice. 
</P>
<P>
 Clare said he hopes the donation will spur others. Donations reduce the need 
for loans and help keep rents low, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (310) 399-4100. KEN ELLINGWOOD 
</P>
</TEXT>
