</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 State school officials have rejected the ABC School District's appeal of a 
county Office of Education decision to send a team of fiscal advisers into the 
district. 
</P>
<P>
 Patrick Keegan, an assistant state superintendent for school business 
services, said ABC officials failed to convince the state that the district had 
resolved its financial problems.ABC officials said they may take their battle 
against the county to court. 
</P>
<P>
