<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: THE REGION; VOLUNTEERS SOUGHT FOR EYEING WEATHER THREATS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The National Weather Service is looking for volunteer spotters to report 
potential mudslide and flood dangers in the foothills of the San Gabriel 
Mountains from Altadena to Monrovia. 
</P>
<P>
 An orientation meeting is scheduled 7 to 9 p.m. Monday at the Community 
Disaster Recovery and Preparedness Center, 3746 Foothill Blvd., Pasadena. At 
future meetings, about 20 volunteers will be trained to spot unusual weather 
conditions and read weather instruments. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (818) 583-7245. 
</P>
</TEXT>
